output: For each test case output on a single line the number of Fibonacci numbers fi with a ≤ fi ≤ b.
input: The input contains several test cases. Each test case consists of two non-negative integer numbers a and b. Input is terminated by a = b = 0.Otherwise, a ≤  b  ≤10100. The numbers a and b are given with no superfluous leading zeros.
name: How many Fibs?
description:
Recall the definition of the Fibonacci numbers:

                    f1 = 1

                    f2 = 2

                    fn = fn-1 + fn-2         (n ≥ 3)

                    Given two numbers a and b, calculate how many Fibonacci numbers are in the range [a,b].
